REPORTS

Statistical interface for Customers, Networks, Gateways

REST call:
GET /report/ReportID?from=YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm&to=YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm
Where
	ReportID - report type, 1 - customer's networks, 2 - network's customers
	YYYY - year
	MM - month
	DD - day
	hh - hours
	mm - minutes

Example:
http://localhost:8080/report/1?from=2012-05-20T00:00&to=2012-02-25T00:00

Result:
<reports>
    <customer>
        <id>feda5822-5271-11e1-bd27-001d0947ec73</id>
        <networks>
            <network>
                <id>920a009a-5270-11e1-b961-001d0947ec73</id>
                <mids>
                    <id>10140</id>
                    <id>10112</id>
                    <id>10178</id>
                </mids>
            </network>
        </networks>
    </customer>
</reports>

Example:
http://localhost:8080/report/2?from=2012-05-20T00:00&to=2012-02-25T00:00

Result:
<reports>
    <network>
        <id>920a009a-5270-11e1-b961-001d0947ec73</id>
        <customers>
            <customer>
                <id>feda5822-5271-11e1-bd27-001d0947ec73</id>
                <mids>
                    <id>10149</id>
                    <id>10126</id>
                    <id>10109</id>
                </mids>
            </customer>
        </customers>
    </network>
</reports>

REST call:
GET /report/gateways?from=YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm&to=YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm
Where
	YYYY - year
	MM - month
	DD - day
	hh - hours
	mm - minutes

Example:
http://localhost:8080/report/gateways?from=2012-05-21T16:00&to=2012-05-25T19:00

Result:


Message status request.

REST call:
GET /message_status/MesID/customer/CustUUID
Where
	MesID - message id
	CustUUID - customer uuid

Example:
http://localhost:8080/message_status/59/customer/feda5822-5271-11e1-bd27-001d0947ec73

Result:
<message>
	<customer_id>feda5822-5271-11e1-bd27-001d0947ec73</customer_id>
	<message_id>59</message_id>
	<status>delivered</status>
</message>